cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a deep convolutional neural network, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses synthetic data, which is generated using photorealistic human body generation software, and this falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with structural attributes of the human figure, which can be considered as a graphics problem, and hence cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance cameras, which can be considered as a multimedia problem, and hence cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
